[The challenge is preventing the superspreading event from happening. Is daily rapid testing of all employees feasible? The ongoing outbreak in Germany associated with a meat packing plant has raised this issue to the forefront.

In another media report submitted by Mary Marshall (<mjm2020@googlemail.com>), as of Fri 26 Jun 2020, there were 2203 confirmed cases at the Toennies meat packing plant and 75 residents of the district (Guetersloh) without a connection to the plant. (https://www.dw.com/en/germany-g%C3%BCtersloh-slaughterhouse-infections-spread-to-community/a-53971931) demonstrating the order of magnitude of the transmission within the meat packing plant and the impact on the surrounding community.

A map of Germany showing states https://www.mapsofworld.com/germany/germany-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7520442,66928. Gutersloh is located in North Rhine-Westphalia. - Mod.MPP]

