Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update (please note that there has been consistent weekend reporting artifact since the presentation of these data began):
-----------------------------------------
The Americas region reported 62.0% of the global newly reported cases and 68.7% of newly reported deaths for this 24-hour period. Brazil reported 40.0% of the newly confirmed cases in the region, and the USA reported 37.9%, Mexico 4.6%, Chile 3.8%, Colombia 3.3%, Peru 3.2%, and Ecuador 2.5%. The same 5 countries remained at the top; the USA and Brazil are usually numbers 1 and 2, although they vary for which of the 2 positions they hold, but other countries are continuing to increase their proportional representation within the region.

The European region reported 8.8% of the global newly reported cases and 7.6% of the newly confirmed deaths in the region. Russia reported 40.9% of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Turkey 8.3%, Ukraine 5.5%, the UK 5.4 %, Armenia 4.4%, Spain 3.4%, Azerbaijan 3.1%,Kazakhstan 2.8%, and Belarus 2.3%. The proportion of cases represented by Russia has fallen. Sweden did not report any newly confirmed cases today. Armenia, Kazakhstan, Azerbaijan, Ukraine, and Belarus are prominent in countries noted to have resurgence in Europe.

The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 9.5% of the global newly reported cases and 10.5% of global newly reported fatalities. Pakistan reported 22.7% of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Saudi Arabia 21.9%, Iran 13.7%, Iraq 11.5%, Egypt 6.5%, Oman 5.1%, Qatar 4.9%, and Kuwait 3.8%. Multiple countries are very active in the region.

The African region reported 5.7% of the global newly reported cases and 2.4% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 67.3% of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Nigeria 7.3%, Ghana 5.6%, and Algeria and Kenya 2.6% each. Other countries of prior prominence are less than 2%. While South Africa and Nigeria are usually numbers 1 and 2 in terms of the 24-hour increase in cases, other countries have less consistent reporting patterns and vary considerably from day to day.

The Western Pacific region reported 0.67% of the global newly reported cases and 0.26% of global deaths. The Philippines reported 58.0% of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Singapore 23.1%, Japan 7.4 %, South Korea 4.9%, Australia 3.7%, and China 1.4%. The outbreak associated with the Beijing Seafood markets continues to bring China to prominence in terms of daily newly confirmed cases. That said, the Philippines and Singapore are consistently numbers 1 and 2, respectively, and the other countries, including Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, and Australia, vary in daily reporting.

The South-East Asia region reported 13.4% of the global newly reported cases and 10.5% of global deaths. India reported 78.4% of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 13.8%, Indonesia 5.4%, and Nepal 2.2%. Same countries, same order as in previous days, with India continuing to be the driving force in the regional growth in cases.

Impression: The ordering of the regions has the Americas having the highest disease load and newly confirmed cases on a daily basis, followed by the South-East Asia region, then Europe and the Eastern Mediterranean alternating on a daily basis of their order, today's major decrease in Europe's reporting may well be weekend reporting artifact, followed by the Africa region and the Western Pacific representing the lowest daily case load of all of the regions.

Figure 2. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases, by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 28 Jun 2020, at the source URL above, is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic as described in the above text. The Americas region continues to increase, as does South-East Asia, in terms of daily newly confirmed cases; the African region is noticeably increasing as well. The Americas region continues to greatly outnumber all other regions for daily reporting. - Mod.MPP]

